data.name: Explanation.Text
data.value: Use this dialog to map source members to destination members. A mapping is between a source (what you have) and a destination (what you want). When the conversion from one or more source members to a destination member is done, the mapping informs the conversion process that the mapped source members are used to populate the destination member using a conversion, or mapping, function. This dialog defines two mappings, a Resource -> Entity mapping and an Entity -> Resource mapping.
